A Case for Bitcoin Alts

Sunny Shi

Dec 6, 2024 ⋅  9 min read

Key Insights

  • The Bitcoin network underwent a paradigm shift with the launch of Runes and Ordinals, leading to the creation of the first generation of alts on mainnet.
  • Although Runes and Ordinals saw a significant decline in activity in the summer months, sustained activity, strong mindshare, and rising valuations seem to indicate a bottom.
  • Upcoming catalysts for Bitcoin alts include strong BTC momentum, Magic Eden’s TGE, improving UX, potential CEX listings, and Chinese economic stimulus.
  • Despite Bitcoin's limitations (e.g., high block times, low programmability), we believe there is asymmetric upside in the broader ecosystem heading into 2025.

Introduction

The Bitcoin network changed forever in 2023 with the introduction of Ordinal Theory. Ordinals enable arbitrary data (images, text, etc.) to be inscribed on an individual satoshi (the smallest divisible unit of Bitcoin), effectively creating tradable and entirely onchain NFTs on Bitcoin mainnet. As a follow up, Casey Rodarmor, the founder of Ordinal Theory, decided to release a fungible Bitcoin token standard called Runes in 2024, essentially replicating the functionality of the Ethereum ERC-20 token standard on the Bitcoin network. With the introduction of these new innovations, the Bitcoin L1 has evolved beyond BTC and now hosts its first ever generation of alternative tokens (alts).

After some initial mania, Bitcoin alts have largely cooled off, leaving the narrative relatively forgotten as ecosystems on chains like Solana and Base have taken much of the attention. However, we believe there is a large opportunity for the narrative to resurge now that it has found a stable floor.

This report will highlight the trends so far for Runes and Ordinals, and what might drive a rerating of this new and exciting crypto sector.

Runes and Ordinals - Where Are They At?

Down but not Out

After peaking at over 700,000 daily transactions in April 2024 shortly after launch, Runes activity has trended downward, stabilizing at approximately 50,000–100,000 daily transactions after June. While these figures are modest compared to the tens of millions of daily transactions on Solana, it’s important to note that Bitcoin’s infrastructure was not originally designed to handle the high throughput of today’s more performant blockchains. Although this remains a source of friction, it is likely that Runes on Bitcoin will adopt a different culture, one centered around holding rather than trading.

Despite this, new addresses continue to engage with Runes for the first time, highlighting sustained interest. Additionally, November mindshare for Runes remains strong, consistently ranking within the top ten for crypto-related discussions according to Kaito AI, and at times breaching the top three, competing directly with high-profile sectors like DeFi.

Early Signs of Revival

Select Runes and Ordinals collections continue to do well and command high valuations. Many of these still represent memetic tokens (in the case of Runes) or NFTs (for Ordinals), given the lack of programmability on the Bitcoin network to facilitate more complicated protocols.

The two leading Runes DOG•GO•TO•THE•MOON (DOG) and PUPS•WORLD•PEACE (PUPS) both command nine-figure market caps and have recovered well from their lows in the summer.

Similarly, leading Ordinals collection Bitcoin Puppets has also seen prices trend higher, now at an impressive ~$16,000 floor price for a standard 10,000 supply collection.

DOG is currently a top 15 memecoin by market capitalization, and Bitcoin Puppets and NodeMonkes are both top 15 NFT collections by collective value (floor price x supply). This means that the Bitcoin L1 now has both a leading memecoin as well as a leading NFT collection. No other blockchain besides Ethereum mainnet and Solana can make the same claim. We believe this is evidence that consumer demand persists for alts on Bitcoin, and that overtime Runes and Ordinals can become strong candidates for renewed broader interest.

Upcoming Growth Drivers

As we head into 2025, we lay out several potential growth drivers and catalysts for a narrative revival.

Bitcoin’s Value Proposition

Growing communities, a fresh narrative, and Bitcoin's cultural significance to crypto create a unique value proposition for Bitcoin alts, especially as the memecoin environment on other chains becomes increasingly rotational and overcrowded. Memecoin buyers seeking new opportunities may find greener pastures on the Bitcoin network as tokens on other chains become overcapitalized. We believe that trading fatigue may gradually drive users on Solana and Ethereum to explore less competitive and earlier-stage ecosystems, with Bitcoin emerging as a compelling alternative. We also give credit to the qualitative narratives in crypto, and being a participant in the first generation of alts on crypto’s oldest and most important chain will be a strong cultural differentiator.

Ecosystem Wealth Effects

There are two potential "wealth effects" on the horizon for the Bitcoin ecosystem. First, Bitcoin's price has surged, crossing the $100,000 mark for the first time just this week. This milestone bodes well for Bitcoin alts. Since Runes and Ordinals are denominated in BTC, and native BTC holders on mainnet have seen their net worth increase—the door is open for them to move further up the risk curve. Overall, we expect that bullish price action for BTC will unlock market demand for BTC-based alts, much like how alts on Ethereum are often viewed as beta to ETH.

The second catalyst is that Magic Eden, the leading Runes and Ordinals exchange, is rapidly approaching its token genesis event (TGE). Eligibility checkers went live on December 4th, and with a pre-market over-the-counter (OTC) valuation of over $3 billion as of writing, the initial $ME airdrop could provide a $375 million stimulus to active Runes and Ordinals users. Additionally, the 37.7% community and ecosystem fund will contribute towards continuous incentives and ecosystem development.

Improving UI/UX

Given that the Bitcoin alts ecosystem is still in its early stages, the user experience has significant room for improvement. Bitcoin block times often exceed 10 minutes, and the lack of DeFi infrastructure means that liquid DEXs for alts are non-existent. Magic Eden has emerged as a key builder in this space, striving to address the current pain points of trading and interacting with these token standards. Their orderbook for the Runes standard continues to grow its liquidity depth, and the user experience for Ordinals has already reached a level comparable to NFT exchanges on other chains. We believe that as development moves forward led by Magic Eden and other influential players like OKX, more capital will be drawn into the ecosystem.

CEX Listings

Last month, the top three Runes were nominated for Binance futures listings. If centralized exchanges (CEXs) begin to list Runes on both futures and spot markets, they would become the most liquid venues to trade them, serving as a key supply unlock. We note that when observing the 105 assets that received Binance futures listings in 2024, the average opening return in the first 12 hours of trading was around 77%. While performance has faltered on a longer timeframe, we predict that listings would be particularly positive for Runes, given the existing friction on mainnet that severely inhibits organic price discovery.

NFT Resurgence

Over the past 90 days, NFT volumes and total market cap have grown by ~140% and ~280% respectively. Given the success of Bitcoin Puppets so far, it is likely that NFT buyers are becoming more chain agnostic, and we see any additional growth in the NFT market to benefit the Ordinals market as well.

Tailwinds in Asia

Ordinals and Runes are particularly popular in China, with Ordinals Asia in Hong Kong standing as the largest global event dedicated to the Bitcoin alts ecosystem. Sentiment in China’s risk markets is drastically improving. In November, Chinese authorities provided significant regulatory clarity on crypto ownership, with a Shanghai court explicitly recognizing the legality of personal Bitcoin holdings. At the same time, Chinese risk assets are appreciating, with the SSE Composite Index up 13% year-to-date amid growing optimism for potential long-term quantitative easing. If speculative appetite and economic conditions continue to ameliorate in China, we believe Bitcoin and its collection of alts could be poised as key beneficiaries down the line.

Risks to the Thesis

Bitcoin’s Limitations

It is possible that the limitations of the Bitcoin network are too frustrating for users to bear. High block times, low liquidity, and inaccessibility may be simply incompatible with an alts ecosystem. However, we point to the continued usage and valuations of Runes and Ordinals as solid indicators that these limitations can be overcome, and think that there is asymmetric upside to consumer adoption from here, especially as protocols like Magic Eden improve overall UX.

Continued Chain and Liquidity Fragmentation

As newly dominant blockchains like Base establish themselves and emerging alt L1s like Sui continue to proliferate, users may begin to experience chain fatigue, making them less inclined to bridge to Bitcoin. With an increasing number of L1 and L2 solutions offering unique ecosystems and incentives, the complexity of managing assets across multiple chains can become overwhelming.

Rejection from Bitcoin Natives

Bitcoin’s native addressable market is one of the largest in crypto, given the amount of value currently housed on the network in native BTC. Even a low single digit conversion rate of that value to alts would be significantly impactful. However, it is possible that BTC holders reject alts entirely, given a fixation on BTC being the only legitimate crypto asset. While we believe it is not necessary to see mass conversion from BTC native holders in order for the ecosystem to find success, a philosophical pushback on the need for alts from Bitcoin maximalists could deal reputational damage.

Conclusion

Bitcoin alts have experienced a significant decline in usage since earlier this year. However, valuations, communities, and mindshare remain strong, with activity leveling out over recent months. Several potential growth drivers could fuel a resurgence in 2025, with an opportunity to be positioned early ahead of a comeback narrative. We see asymmetric upside present, as the ecosystem appears to have largely reached a bottom.
